Hundreds of Kisumu residents yesterday benefited from free legal advice by the Law Society of Kenya at the Jomo Kenyatta Sports Ground. The two-day exercise is done to observe the Legal Awareness Week.It concludes today. It commenced countrywide on Monday. The theme is Improving Access to Justice through Alternative Dispute Resolution . LSK branch chairman Francis Olel said the public receives free legal advice on land cases, alternative dispute resolution, succession and family laws.He said the society has a role to provide information and advise clients on legal issues. Olel urged the public to come out in large numbers to benefit from the services.LSK Kisumu branch will also visit Kodiaga Prison to offer services to inmates. He said this is one of ways of giving back to society Olel because majority are not able to afford legal services.